    <p>The conformance of your service is required to be stated in <a href="/accessibility/accessibility-statements">accessibility statements</a> so it's important that it's correct.</p>

    <p>WCAG-EM is for evaluating <a href="/accessibility/determine-conformance">conformance</a> of websites.</p>

    <div class="govuk-inset-text">Design Ops are working on a service to complete conformance assurance reports.</div>

     <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Methodology</h2>

    <div class="dfeuk-timeline">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Scope of audit</h3>
                <p>The name and areas of the website to be audited.</p>
                <p>Scope also includes the WCAG version and conformance to be tested </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Understand the website</h3>
                <p>Review pages in the website and identify any web technologies to test. Including:</p>
                <ul class="govuk-list">
                    <li>HTML</li>
                    <li>CSS</li>
                    <li>ARIA</li>
                    <li>JavaScript</li>
                    <li>SVG</li>
                    <li>PDF</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Define the sample</h3>
                <p>What pages of the user journey are to be tested based on the scope.</p>
                <p>Select a random sample of 5 pages that are not part of the main journey to test.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Audit the website</h3>
                <p>Audit each page against each of the success criteria for the selected WCAG version and conformance level.</p>
                <p>Record findings for pages tested/</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Report findings</h3>
                <p>Generate and publish report identifying risks and opportunities.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

